summary: Use this api to fetch the logistics information of an order, these info can be used for airwaybill printing
description: Use this api to fetch the logistics information of an order, these info can be used for airwaybill printing. May not be applicable for local channel airwaybill. Besides, this api supports returning personal info as images.

query.name: order_sn
query.description: Shopee's unique identifier for an order.

query.name: package_number
query.description: Shopee's unique identifier for the package under an order. You shouldn't fill the field with empty string when there isn't a package number.

query.name: recipient_address_info
query.description: recipient address to query as image

query.name: key
query.description: fields to query in the recipient address, should be name, phone, full_address, town, district, city, state, region, zipcode.

query.name: h_align
query.description: text horizontal align, supports left, center and right.

request_examples.code:
<?php

$curl = curl_init();

curl_setopt_array($curl, array(
  CURLOPT_URL => 'https://partner.shopeemobile.com/api/v2/logistics/get_shipping_document_data_info?access_token=access_token&partner_id=partner_id&shop_id=shop_id&sign=sign&timestamp=timestamp',
  CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER => true,
  CURLOPT_ENCODING => '',
  CURLOPT_MAXREDIRS => 10,
  CURLOPT_TIMEOUT => 0,
  CURLOPT_FOLLOWLOCATION => true,
  CURLOPT_HTTP_VERSION => CURL_HTTP_VERSION_1_1,
  CURLOPT_CUSTOMREQUEST => 'POST',
  CURLOPT_POSTFIELDS => '{
    "order_sn": "201224EM1FMFG1",
    "package_number": "9087129345",
    "recipient_address_info": [
        {
            "key": "name",
            "style": {
                "font_size": 12,
                "h_align": "center",
                "image_width": 3,
                "text_color": "#39c5bb",
                "text_style": [
                    "bold",
                    "italic"
                ]
            }
        }
    ]
}',
  CURLOPT_HTTPHEADER => array(
    'Content-Type: application/json'
  ),
));

$response = curl_exec($curl);

curl_close($curl);
echo $response;

schema.name: service_code
schema.description: Only work for cross-border order. This code is required at some sorting hub. Please ensure the service_code is INCLUDED on your shipping label, otherwise the parcel cannot be processed by the warehouse. If you didn't retrieve service_code after you first called this API, please try few more times within 30 minutes.

schema.name: first_mile_name
schema.description: Only work for cross-border order.The name of the carrier ships cross country or region.

schema.name: last_mile_name
schema.description: Only work for cross-border order.The name of the carrier delivers the parcels in local country or region.

schema.name: goods_to_declare
schema.description: Only work for cross-border order.This value indicates whether the order contains goods that are required to declare at customs. "T" means true and it will mark as "T" on the shipping label; "F" means false and it will mark as "P" on the shipping label. This value is accurate ONLY AFTER the order trackingNo is generated, please capture this value AFTER your retrieve the trackingNo.

schema.name: lane_code
schema.description: Only work for cross-border order. The string use for waybill printing. The format is "S - region_code and lane_number". For example, S-TH01, S-TH02

schema.name: mutual_check
schema.description: only apply for ID/VN shops. mutual_check indicates whether the parcel is eligible for Return-on-the-Spot (RoS) co-check. If mutual_check=1, then the parcel is RoS eligible, where drivers and buyers can co-check the parcel. Buyer can then choose to accept or reject the parcel on the spot. If mutual_check=0, then the parcel is ineligible for RoS.

schema.name: dely_fri_label
schema.description: Probability of Successful Friday Delivery. The value of L(low), M(medium), H(high) represent the chances of successful delivery attempts on Friday.

schema.name: dely_sat_label
schema.description: Probability of Successful Saturday Delivery The value of L(low), M(medium), H(high) represent the chances of successful delivery attempts on Saturday.

schema.name: dely_sun_label
schema.description: Probability of Successful Sunday Delivery. The value of L(low), M(medium), H(high) represent the chances of successful delivery attempts on Sunday.

schema.name: pickup_code
schema.description: For drivers to quickly identify parcel to be picked up. Only returned for ID and TH local orders which use instant+sameday for delivery.
